title: Strictly’s Saffron Barker and AJ Pritchard top the leaderboard in shock result
text:
Saffron Barker has hit the top of the leaderboard (Picture: PA)

Saffron Barker and AJ Pritchard shot to the top of the leaderboard for the first time on Strictly Come Dancing.

The 19-year-old YouTuber performed the Foxtrot to the theme from New York, New York, by Frank Sinatra, achieving her best scores of the competition so far.

Speaking after the dance, judge Motsi Mabuse said: ‘I think she did really, really well. This is a big iconic song that needs a big personality to fill it in, and I think you lived up to that song.

‘You gave me beautiful technique, you gave me music, you gave me everything I needed to end the show. Congratulations.’

Temporary judge, Alfonso Ribeiro said: ‘That was awesome. Your rise and fall was spectacular. I loved it, you hit it with a bang.’

Craig Revel Horwood added: ‘Technically I thought it was absolutely brilliant. You really surprised me tonight, I have to say.’

Strictly Come Dancing week five leaderboard Saffron Barker & AJ Pritchard – 38 points Karim Zeroual & Amy Dowden – 36 points Emma Weymouth & Aljaz Skorjanec – 36 points Alex Scott & Neil Jones – 33 points Kelvin Fletcher & Oti Mabuse – 33 points Will Bayley & Janette Manrara – 32 points Michelle Visage & Giovanni Pernice – 29 points Catherine Tyldesley & Johannes Radebe – 28 points Emma Barton & Anton Du Beke – 26 points Chris Ramsey & Karen Hauer – 25 points Mike Bushell and Katya Jones – 21 points David James & Nadiya Bychkova – 16 points

Saffron earned a 9, 10, 9, 10 from the judges, topping the leaderboard with 38 points above Karim Zeroual and Emma Weymouth in joint second place.

Speaking after the performance, Saffron said: ‘I like ballroom, I think ballroom is going to be more my thing than Latin.’

Strictly Come Dancing continues on BBC One on Sunday.
